spec: socket_extra162
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra161.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.send/__recv/__sendto/__recvfrom qualname strings and lengths / all four are method_descriptor (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra160.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.bind/__listen/__accept/__close qualname strings and lengths / bind and listen are method_descriptor / accept and close are function (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra159.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__module__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__bases__[0].__name__/__module__ / socket.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.__init__') / socket.connect.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.connect') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra158.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) / AF_INET6.__eq__(30) / SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) / SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) / AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') / SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SocketKind') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') / socket.socket makefile/__setblocking/__settimeout/__getpeername/__getsockname/__setsockopt qualnames and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra161."
    - "Wave 344 theme: socket.socket dunder method qualnames — __repr__/__str__/__enter__/__exit__ qualname strings and lengths; __repr__/__enter__/__exit__ are Python 'function' (defined in Lib/socket.py); __str__ is 'wrapper_descriptor' (inherited from object via 'object.__str__' qualname); qualname lengths: __str__(14) < __repr__==__exit__(15) < __enter__(16)."
    - "socket.socket.__repr__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__repr__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__str__.__qualname__ == 'object.__str__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__enter__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__enter__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__exit__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__exit__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__repr__.__qualname__.__len__() == 15. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__str__.__qualname__.__len__() == 14. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__enter__.__qualname__.__len__() == 16. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__exit__.__qualname__.__len__() == 15. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__str__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__enter__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__exit__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__repr__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__repr__' (15 chars = 'socket.'=7 + '__repr__'=8). socket.socket defines its own __repr__ as a Python function in Lib/socket.py; it returns a string showing the socket fileno and address family. socket.socket.__repr__ is a 'function' (not a 'wrapper_descriptor'), meaning it is defined in Python, not inherited from a C class. Extra159 anchors socket.__init__ at 15 chars and connect at 14 chars; 'socket.__repr__' (15 chars) ties socket.__init__ at 15 chars."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__str__.__qualname__ == 'object.__str__' (14 chars = 'object.'=7 + '__str__'=7). Unlike __repr__ which is defined on socket.socket itself, __str__ is NOT overridden in socket.socket. It is inherited from the built-in object class, so its qualname shows 'object.__str__' with the 'object.' prefix. __str__ is a 'wrapper_descriptor' (the type for C-level special methods inherited from object). 'object.__str__' (14 chars) is 1 char shorter than 'socket.__repr__' (15 chars)."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__enter__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__enter__' (16 chars = 'socket.'=7 + '__enter__'=9). socket.socket defines __enter__ as a Python function to support the context manager protocol (with socket.socket() as s:). __enter__ simply returns self. '__enter__'=9 chars = '__'=2 + 'enter'=5 + '__'=2. 'socket.__enter__' (16 chars) is the longest dunder qualname in this spec. All three context manager/representation methods (__repr__, __enter__, __exit__) are Python 'function' type (defined in Lib/socket.py)."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__exit__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__exit__' (15 chars = 'socket.'=7 + '__exit__'=8). __exit__ is the context manager cleanup method. When the 'with' block exits (normally or via exception), __exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) is called to close the socket. '__exit__'=8 chars = '__'=2 + 'exit'=4 + '__'=2. 'socket.__exit__' (15 chars) ties 'socket.__repr__' (15 chars). Length ordering: __str__(14) < __repr__==__exit__(15) < __enter__(16)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

